        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-10-18T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-10-18T14:00:00-05:00" n="293" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d293">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.35/10–1845: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cabot</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Buenos Aires</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-10-18T16:00:00-03:00">October 18, 1945—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received October 18—2:48 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2577. Would appreciate immediate instructions as to whether I am to continue
                    relations with Argentine Government. I see little legal excuse for withdrawing
                    recognition but question of our position in event of civil war makes
                    consideration this problem appear advisable.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cabot</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
